# Copy to .env.local to override the API the frontend talks to.
#
# Unset, the app talks to the deployed backend on Railway — so `npm run dev`
# works with no local backend at all. Note that this means local dev reads and
# writes PRODUCTION data.
#
# To run against a local backend instead, start it (`npm run dev` in
# "Recipe Hub Backend", which listens on the PORT in its own .env) and set:
#
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5001
#
# The /api suffix is added automatically, and a trailing slash is fine.
